Pancakes

1 cup  all-purpose flour
¼ teaspoon salt
2 teaspoons baking powder
4 tablespoons sugar
2 tablespoons oil or butter, divided
1 cup  water
1 egg or ¼ of oil

Directions:
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and sugar until combined. 
Mix oil or butter, water and egg. 
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients and mix until batter is formed.
Heat skillet over medium heat and add butter or oil. Pour mix into pan and cook until bubbly, flip and cook until browned, 1 to 2 minutes.
